\frac1{n^2}\le \frac1{n(n-1)}=\frac1{n-1}-\frac1n\implies
\sum_{k=2}^n\frac1{k^2}\le\sum_{k=2}^n\left(\frac1{n-1}-\frac1n\right)=1-\frac12+\frac12-\frac13+\ldots+\frac1{n-1}-\frac1n=1-\frac1n\xrightarrow[n\to\infty]{}1
